cs.DC, cs.AR, cs.PF, cs.PL, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses synchronization primitives for GPUs, which are commonly used in parallel computing. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is also likely as the paper analyzes the performance of synchronization primitives on different GPU architectures. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is relevant as the paper evaluates the performance of different synchronization algorithms on GPUs. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses the implementation of synchronization primitives in CUDA, a programming language commonly used for GPU programming. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the behavior of synchronization primitives in the context of the GPU memory system.
